ere uneasy in the wake of the extremely brutal German wartime occupation of Poland, postwar Polish prosecutions of German Nazis placed emphasis on the fate of Jews during the Holocaust. Justice Behind the Iron Curtain is the first work to approach communist Poland’s judicial postwar confrontation with the legacy of the Nazi occupation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCommunismzPolandxHistoryy20th century. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945). 0aNaziszPolandxHistoryy20th century. 0aWar crime trialszPolandxHistoryy20th century. 0aWar criminalszPolandxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh  aHolocaust.  aJewish.  aNazism.  aPoland.  aWorld War II.  acommunism.  alaw.  amemory.  apostwar.  awar crimes trials.1 aPrusin, Alexander , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060679940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144262537240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442625372423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442625372.jpg  a978-3-11-060679-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles